ass=m><span class=title> Re: hey ... LAAAAAAGGG!!!!</span><hr size=1> I'm sure turning down the resolution helps a tiny bit but there are other tricks that do a better job. /effects none is the first thing you want to do.<br>
<br>
The next is to get the smallest percent of your screen covered by players. Drawing other players is the most expensive thing the computer does so the less on the screen and the less space they take up, the higher your framerate.<br>
<br>
Looking straight at the ground, or zooming out as much as possible and angling the camera help out as well. <p><table width="600" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
