I was on an Athlon 1400GHz w 1GB RAM and a GF3 and I still couldn't move. <p><CENTER><TABLE cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><TD colspan=2><HR></TD></TR><TR valign=top><TD align=right><FONT Size=5><B><u>Chemistrius Ul'Veldrin   </u></B></FONT><BR><FONT size=-1>60<sup>th</Sup> Season Dark Elf Assassin<BR>Officer of Requiem of Souls</FONT></TD><TD><FONT size=-2>It will be a hard life.<BR>One without remorse, without reward, without regret.<BR>A path will be placed before you, the choice is yours alone.<BR>Do what you think you cannot do.<BR>It will be a hard life, but you will find out who you are.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD colspan=2><HR></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uczeris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Czeris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 12:27:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2119.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hey ... LAAAAAAGGG!!!!</span><hr size=1> There's not a system on the planet that can handle drawing 200 different characters at the same time.  It's not Mythic, it's just the way it is.<br>
<br>
A low end system like mine can handle about 30 people on screen before it starts chugging.  I've played on a couple different 1.5 gig systems, and they start chugging at 60-90 people.  200 is lights out for any system.<br>
<br>
/effects none is a good start.  It cuts down on a lot of the stuff that your system has to draw.  More RAM never hurts either and is cheap.<br>
<br>
Maybe the next or next next generations of graphics cards, and systems will be able to handle that many people, but it's just not there yet.<br>
<br>
The only other viable solution would be for Mythic to allow some way of seriously simplifying the graphics in huge battle conditions, but that ain't going to happen anytime soon.  I personally would have no problem just seeing red blocks for invaders, and blue blocks for friends in extreme circumstances (like 150+ battles), if it meant I could actually move.  It's to the point where I don't even go near really large battles, since I am effectively useless.  Hit f8, /stick, f6 and hope you hit something.  That's not fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umjnorman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mjnorman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 12:28:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2119.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> this might help</span><hr size=1> I was getting lag last night in an emain scuffle so I decided to try the new effects switch they put in last patch.  It works like this:<br>
<br>
turn effects on = /effects all<br>
turn effects off = /effects none (or /effects self)<br>
<br>
It worked like a champ. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uczeris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Czeris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 12:30:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2119.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hey ... LAAAAAAGGG!!!!</span><hr size=1> Lisboa: you don't participate in the middle of the battles.  Do like I do and stalk around the edges.  It's more complementary of our abilities anyway.<br>
